This paper is about instance segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method, EmbedMask, uses embedding modules to generate embeddings for pixels and proposals, which is a common technique in deep learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance and speed of the method, which are topics related to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The method is built on top of detection models, which are commonly used in robotics and autonomous systems (cs.RO). Finally, the paper mentions the availability of code, which suggests that it may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) research.
